25 /*
26  * DSP Feature Configuration Macro:
27  * 1. __DSP_PRESENT: Define whether Digital Signal Processing Unit(DSP) is present or not
28  * * 0: Not present
29  * * 1: Present
30  */
31 #ifdef __cplusplus
32  extern "C" {
33 #endif

416 /* ===== Inline Function Start for 3.1. ADD8 ===== */
449 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE unsigned long __RV_ADD8(unsigned long a, unsigned long b)
450 {
451  unsigned long result;
452  __ASM volatile("add8 %0, %1, %2" : "=r"(result) : "r"(a), "r"(b));
453  return result;
454 }
455 /* ===== Inline Function End for 3.1. ADD8 ===== */

631 /* ===== Inline Function Start for 3.6. BITREVI ===== */
665 #define __RV_BITREVI(a, b) \
666  ({ \
667  unsigned long result; \
668  unsigned long __a = (unsigned long)(a); \
669  __ASM volatile("bitrevi %0, %1, %2" : "=r"(result) : "r"(__a), "K"(b)); \
670  result; \
671  })
672 /* ===== Inline Function End for 3.6. BITREVI ===== */

1368 #define __RV_INSB(t, a, b) \
1369  ({ \
1370  unsigned long __t = (unsigned long)(t); \
1371  unsigned long __a = (unsigned long)(a); \
1372  __ASM volatile("insb %0, %1, %2" : "+r"(__t) : "r"(__a), "K"(b)); \
1373  __t; \
1374  })
1375 /* ===== Inline Function End for 3.22. INSB ===== */

24550 // For now, the P-extention version of IAR IDE is 0.5.0, but Nuclei's supports 0.5.4
24551 // so Nuclei supplies a workround to add custom instructions of those not natively
24552 // supported by the IAR Assembler. Note that __RV_BPICK remains to be implemented in future.
24553 // And we only implement Xxldsp Nuclei custom instruction set, bpick not implemented, expdxx
24554 // implemented in c, not via .insn variant
24555 
24556 #pragma inline=forced_no_body
24557 unsigned long __RV_STAS16(unsigned long a, unsigned long b) {
24558  unsigned long r;
24559  __asm(".insn r 0x7F, 0x2, 0x7A, %0,%1,%2":"=r"(r) : "r"(a), "r"(b) );
24560  return r;
24561 }
24562

24568 }

24759 /* XXXXX ARM Compatiable SIMD API XXXXX */
24761 #define __QADD8(x, y) __RV_KADD8(x, y)
24763 #define __QSUB8(x, y) __RV_KSUB8((x), (y))
24765 #define __QADD16(x, y) __RV_KADD16((x), (y))
24767 #define __SHADD16(x, y) __RV_RADD16((x), (y))
24769 #define __QSUB16(x, y) __RV_KSUB16((x), (y))
24771 #define __SHSUB16(x, y) __RV_RSUB16((x), (y))
24773 #define __QASX(x, y) __RV_KCRAS16((x), (y))
24775 #define __SHASX(x, y) __RV_RCRAS16((x), (y))
24777 #define __QSAX(x, y) __RV_KCRSA16((x), (y))
24779 #define __SHSAX(x, y) __RV_RCRSA16((x), (y))
24781 #define __SMUSDX(x, y) __RV_SMXDS((y), (x))
24783 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE long __SMUADX (unsigned long op1, unsigned long op2)
24784 {
24785  return __RV_KMXDA(op1, op2);
24786 }
24788 #define __QADD(x, y) __RV_KADDW((x), (y))
24790 #define __QSUB(x, y) __RV_KSUBW((x), (y))
24792 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE long __SMLAD(unsigned long op1, unsigned long op2, long acc)
24793 {
24794  return __RV_KMADA(acc, op1, op2);
24795 }
24797 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE long __SMLADX(unsigned long op1, unsigned long op2, long acc)
24798 {
24799  return __RV_KMAXDA(acc, op1, op2);
24800 }
24802 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE long __SMLSDX(unsigned long op1, unsigned long op2, long acc)
24803 {
24804  return (acc - __RV_SMXDS(op1, op2));
24805 }
24807 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE long long __SMLALD(unsigned long op1, unsigned long op2, long long acc)
24808 {
24809  return __RV_SMALDA(acc, op1, op2);
24810 }
24812 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE long long __SMLALDX(unsigned long op1, unsigned long op2, long long acc)
24813 {
24814  return __RV_SMALXDA(acc, op1, op2);
24815 }
24817 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE long __SMUAD(unsigned long op1, unsigned long op2)
24818 {
24819  return __RV_KMDA(op1, op2);
24820 }
24822 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE long __SMUSD(unsigned long op1, unsigned long op2)
24823 {
24824  return __RV_SMDRS(op1, op2);
24825 }
24827 #define __SXTB16(x) __RV_SUNPKD820(x)
24829 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE unsigned long __SXTAB16(unsigned long op1, unsigned long op2)
24830 {
24831  return __RV_ADD16(op1, __RV_SUNPKD820(op2));
24832 }
24833 #define __SXTAB16_RORn(ARG1, ARG2, ROTATE) __SXTAB16(ARG1, __ROR(ARG2, ROTATE))
24834 
24836 __STATIC_FORCEINLINE long __SMMLA(long op1, long op2, long acc)
24837 {
24838  long mul;
24839  mul = __RV_SMMUL(op1, op2);
24840  return (acc + mul);
24841 }
